PrecisRegulations Amending the MIGRATORY BIRDS REGULATIONS by introducing and defining the term "farmland", setting out the criteria to be used by Regional Directors to evaluate requests and to make decisions concerning the issuance of hunting permits, removing references to species (Ross' Geese) that are not overabundant, and by expanding the special conservation season to include the whole of southern Manitoba.
